# Active Directory Deployment

## Project Overview
What is an Active Directory?
  Active Directory (AD) is the backbone of almost every corporate IT environment in the world.
  It manages all the System Operations, Network, Databases of an Organization Managing Seurity and Company policies.

## Tools Need
  Hypervisor: VMware Workstation
  Virtual Machines: Windows Server and Windows 10 ISO

## FOLLOW THE SEQUENCE
  Phase 1: Build the Virtual Machines
          - Download VMware Workstation Pro from Broadcom Website
          - Download Windows Server ISO and Windows 10

  Phase 2: Configure the Machines
          - Configure the Windows Server and Windows 10 in the Hypervisor Individually
          - Assign a Static IP Address to the Windows Server because server needs to stay in one place clients need to access them

  Phase 3: Building the Domain
          - On the Windows Server you need to install a role Active Directory (AD). After Installation prompt the sever to Doamin Controller

  Phase 4: Joining the Domain
          - Login to the Windows 10 client machine. Point its DNS to the Windows Server IP Address and officially join the machine

  Phase 5: Active Directory Policy Management
          - Back on the Windows server open AD users and computers accounts 
          - Login in using new AD Credentials
          - Add Groups and Policies, Set Rights and Permissions for every single computer on the Active Directory

Hence you can manage computer and users in any organization/company centrally by limiting access for the specific work type

